Thalia Sales to Top EU1 Billion This Year, Wirtschaftswoche Says

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-10-14T18:08:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/thalia-sales-to-top-eu1-billion-this-year-wirtschaftswoche-says.html
Thalia, the German bookstore chain
owned by  Douglas Holding AG (DOU) , will likely reach sales of more
than 1 billion euros ($1.38 billion) for the first time this
year,  Wirtschaftswoche  said, citing an interview with Michael Busch, the board member at Douglas responsible for its books
business.  To contact the reporter on this story:
